# Enforce LF on checkout on EVERY platform.
#
# Warden's content addressing hashes the raw bytes of each file (SKILL.md,
# manifests, etc.), and signatures cover that digest. If git rewrote line
# endings to CRLF on a Windows clone, the re-derived digest would not match the
# signed digest and `warden verify-all` would fail on a fresh checkout. Forcing
# LF keeps the bytes identical everywhere, so signatures verify on clone.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never apply EOL normalization.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
